<FrameLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context="com.scowluga.android.msccareershowcase.details.ResponsibilitiesFragment">

    <!-- TODO: Update blank fragment layout -->
    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        style="@style/LayoutParams">


        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:orientation="vertical">

            <TextView
                style="@style/infoText"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="@dimen/marginOut"
                android:text="Working up to almost 20 hours a week, I had varying duties as listed below."/>


            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="1. Perform system configurations through setup and installation of various software on devices, assisting in preparation such that the user can directly begin use upon receiving. Uses various PowerShell and command scripts."

                />

            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="2. Create product web pages and assist in development of the MCS website through HTML, CSS, and Javascript. "

                />


            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="3. Create constant contact emails for various marketing campaign, assisting in distribution of assistive software to schools and individual patrons across Canada. "

                />


            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="4. Understand and learn key points about products to assist in marketing and media development (website). "

                />


            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="5. Assist in various other duties including hardware replacement, troubleshooting, etc. "

                />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                style="@style/infoText"
                android:layout_marginTop="16dp"
                android:text="Through the placement, I have developed and built upon 3 essential skills."/>

            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="1. Organization - Taking note and keeping track of all items on the sales order of a configuration. "

                />

            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="2. Problem Solving - Encountering and working through various problems such as product malfunctions and defections. "

                />

            <TextView
                style="@style/listItem"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="3. Detail Oriented Work - Accurately keeping track of and documenting process of configuration, specifically including serial numbers and keys. "

                />
        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</FrameLayout>
